params.tokenAddress: The address of the token to be activated.

addToken(address,address).details: Adds a new token to the contract with the specified token and handler addresses.

params.handlerAddress: The address of the handler contract for the specified token.
params.tokenAddress: The address of the token to add.

burnCelo().details: Burns CELO tokens according to burnFraction.

params.test: Set to true to skip implementation initialisation.

params.amountToBurn: The amount of the token to burn.
params.token: The address of the token to query.

dailySellLimitHit(address,uint256).return: Returns true if burning amountToBurn would exceed the daily limit.

deactivateToken(address).details: Deactivates the specified token by marking it as inactive.

params.tokenAddress: The address of the token to deactivate.

distribute(address).details: Distributes the available tokens for the specified token address to the fee beneficiary.

params.tokenAddress: The address of the token for which to distribute the available tokens.

distributeAll().details: Distributes the available tokens for all registered tokens to the feeBeneficiary.

params.token: The address of the token to query.

getPastBurnForToken(address).return: The amount burned for a token.

getTokenActive(address).details: Returns a boolean indicating whether the specified token is active or not.

params.tokenAddress: The address of the token for which to retrieve the active status.

getTokenActive(address).return: A boolean representing the active status of the specified token.

getTokenCurrentDaySellLimit(address).details: Returns the current daily sell limit for the specified token.

params.tokenAddress: The address of the token for which to retrieve the current daily limit.

getTokenCurrentDaySellLimit(address).return: The current daily limit as a uint256 value.

getTokenDailySellLimit(address).details: Returns the daily burn limit for the specified token.

params.tokenAddress: The address of the token for which to retrieve the daily burn limit.

getTokenDailySellLimit(address).return: The daily burn limit as a uint256 value.

getTokenHandler(address).details: Returns the handler address for the specified token.

params.tokenAddress: The address of the token for which to return the handler.

getTokenHandler(address).return: The address of the handler contract for the specified token.

getTokenMaxSlippage(address).details: Returns the maximum slippage percentage for the specified token.

params.tokenAddress: The address of the token for which to retrieve the maximum slippage percentage.

getTokenMaxSlippage(address).return: The maximum slippage percentage as a uint256 value.

getTokenToDistribute(address).details: Returns the amount of tokens available to distribute for the specified token.

params.tokenAddress: The address of the token for which to retrieve the amount of tokens available to distribute.

getTokenToDistribute(address).return: The amount of tokens available to distribute as a uint256 value.

getVersionNumber().return: Storage version of the contract.Major version of the contract.Minor version of the contract.Patch version of the contract.

handle(address).details: Distributes the the token for to the feeBeneficiary.

handleAll().details: Distributes the available tokens for all registered tokens to the feeBeneficiary.

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

sell(address).details: Sets the burn fraction to the specified value. Token has to have a handler set.

params.tokenAddress: The address of the token to sell

setBurnFraction(uint256).details: Sets the burn fraction to the specified value.

params.fraction: The value to set as the burn fraction.

params.newLimit: The new limit to set, in the token units.
params.token: Address of the token to set.

setFeeBeneficiary(address).details: Sets the fee beneficiary address to the specified address.

params.beneficiary: The address to set as the fee beneficiary.

params.handlerAddress: The address of the handler contract to be set.
params.tokenAddress: The address of the token to set the handler for.

params.newMax: New sllipage to set, as Fixidity fraction.
params.token: Address of the token to set.

params.registryAddress: The address of a registry contract for routing to other contracts.

params.recipient: The address of the recipient to transfer the tokens to.
params.token: The address of the token to transfer.
params.value: The amount of tokens to transfer.

transfer(address,address,uint256).return: A boolean indicating whether the transfer was successful or not.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

activateToken(address).notice: Allows the owner to activate a specified token.
